This paper proposes new weak memory models for the RISC-V ISA, which is primarily a programming language and architecture topic (cs.PL). However, the paper also discusses the operational definitions and implementation of these models, which falls under computer architecture (cs.AR) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions cache coherence and out-of-order processors, which are topics in computer systems (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
